# Todo App

This is a simple Todo App built with Node.js, Express, and Swagger for API documentation.

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Node.js installed
- MongoDB installed and running
- NPM (Node Package Manager) installed

### Server Setup

1. **Clone the repository:**

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/todo-app.git
Navigate to the server directory:

bash
Copy code
cd todo-app/server

Copy code
npm install
Set up MongoDB:

Make sure MongoDB is running.

Create a .env file in the server directory and add your MongoDB connection URL:

makefile
Copy code
MONGODB_URI=your-mongodb-connection-url
Start the server:

bash
Copy code
npm start
The server will be running at http://localhost:4000.

Client Setup
Open a new terminal window.

Navigate to the client directory:

bash
Copy code
cd todo-app/client
Install dependencies:

bash
Copy code
npm install
Start the client:

bash
Copy code
npm start
The client will be running at http://localhost:3000.

Access Swagger API Documentation
Open a web browser and go to http://localhost:4000/api-docs to access Swagger API documentation.

Explore the API endpoints and test them using Swagger UI.

Feel free to replace "your-username" and customize the instructions based on your specific project structure or requirements.